<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.2.5-6_0001" />

<opener>
<dateline>
Barrytown, N. Y.<lb/>

June 28: 1911 &#8212;
</dateline>

<salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
</opener>
<p>I have just re read your review of my "Learning + other Essays" in the <title>Sunday Times</title>. I knew from your letter that the review would be favorable; but I was not prepared for such a blast nor have I ever had anything like it. By some <unclear>likeness of finer history</unclear> the Essays mean to you what I meant them to say.</p>

<pb facs="nei.j4a.2.5-6_0002"/>

<p>But what a wonderful coincidence that this man should be chosen to review the volume! And how much more <del>it is</del><add>am I getting</add> than any man has a right to expect in the way what <hi rend="underline">he</hi> thinks is understanding of his work. Thank you &#8212; or rather Thank You for the <unclear>consideration.</unclear></p>
<closer>
<salute>Your <unclear/></salute>

<signed>John Jay Chapman</signed>
</closer>
</div1>
